{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_25","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-5703-fails-java-run-com.lihaoyi-fansi_3-0.5.1-15be482e\n\nThe original `fails-java-run` failure was two JVM assertion failures in `Fansi_3Test` (`expected: <0> but was: <-2147483648>` and `expected: <0> but was: <2147483648>`) in `logs/com.lihaoyi:fansi_3:0.5.1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-06T04-26-57-301211Z.log`. The preserved candidate appears to fix that: later runs report `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`, `11 tests successful`, and passing `nativeTest` in `logs/com.lihaoyi:fansi_3:0.5.1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-06T04-32-14-745420Z.log`, `logs/com.lihaoyi:fansi_3:0.5.1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-06T04-32-55-676617Z.log`, and `logs/com.lihaoyi:fansi_3:0.5.1/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-06T04-30-52-304204Z.log`.\n\nThe most likely stage that actually failed the workflow is `native-test-verify` metadata generation, not the test fix itself. In `logs/com.lihaoyi:fansi_3:0.5.1/native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-2026-05-06T04-30-48-448487Z.log`, `:generateMetadata` fails because the JVM cannot load `native-image-agent` (`Could not find agent library native-image-agent ... libnative-image-agent.so: cannot open shared object file`), which also explains why dynamic-access coverage is unavailable. The metrics file `stats/com.lihaoyi/fansi_3/0.5.1/execution-metrics.json` still records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, and `artifacts.test_file: None`, even though the preserved candidate commit `98a5eb2b07f306f53e6d1a5c5f8305a704b6314b` contains a test fix; the generation session is also captured in `logs/com.lihaoyi:fansi_3:0.5.1/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-06T04-29-23-466886Z.log`.\n\nNext steps:\n1. Re-run `generateMetadata` / native verify on the preserved branch after fixing the local GraalVM `native-image-agent` setup.\n2. Review the preserved candidate diff and, if the environment issue is confirmed, promote or cherry-pick the test fix from commit `98a5eb2b07f306f53e6d1a5c5f8305a704b6314b`.\n3. If the rerun stays green, update or repair metrics/artifact capture so the successful test file is recorded instead of `artifacts.test_file: None`."}}
